<title>UK: FOCUS-Predators seen circling  Ivory&amp;Sime.</title>
<headline>FOCUS-Predators seen circling  Ivory&amp;Sime.</headline>
<byline>Caroline Brothers</byline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>The sudden departure of Colin Hook, chief of prestigious Edinburgh fund manager Ivory &amp; Sime, means predators may well start circling soon despite denials that the firm is up for sale, industry sources said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Hook quit suddenly as managing director of the fund management firm on Monday and left immediately because of alleged difficulties in his relationship with fund managers, four of whom quit last month to set up their own firm.</p>
